<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1436,1066,2012]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,327,1066,1092]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Carico. A" authorityYear="1981" box="[334,521,1066,1091]" class="Arachnida" family="Pisauridae" genus="Architis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robusta">
<emphasis box="[334,521,1066,1091]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Architis robusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is close to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos" authorityYear="2007" baseAuthorityName="Mello-Leitao" baseAuthorityYear="2007" box="[655,822,1066,1091]" class="Arachnida" family="Pisauridae" genus="Pisaurina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brasiliensis" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[655,822,1066,1091]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">A. brasiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[830,964,1066,1092]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[830,964,1066,1092]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Carico. A" authorityYear="1981" box="[1022,1185,1066,1091]" class="Arachnida" family="Pisauridae" genus="Architis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="capricorna">
<emphasis box="[1022,1185,1066,1091]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">A. capricorna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with which it shares an elongated embolus coiled under the DTP (partially seen through the transparent cuticle; 
<figureCitation box="[1252,1365,1106,1132]" captionStart="FIGURES 16" captionStartId="30.[151,269,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[239,1362,626,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-209@30.[217,1370,606,1871]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURES 16A–D. Architis robusta Carico. A, male pedipalpus, ventral view; B, male pedipalpus, lateral view; C, female epigynum, ventral view; D, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. The arrow points to the retrolateral projection of the VTA. The embolus can be seen arising close to conductor and through the transparent DTP. Scale bars: A–B, 0.2 mm; C–D, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097223/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Figs 16A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1380,1430,1106,1132]" captionStart="FIGURES 18" captionStartId="33.[151,269,1852,1876]" captionTargetBox="[151,1420,193,1790]" captionTargetId="figure-92@33.[140,1447,152,1828]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURES 18A–F. Architis brasiliensis (Mello-Leitão). A, female habitus, dorsal view; B, female prosoma, frontal view; C, male pedipalpus, ventral view, D, male pedipalpus, lateral view, E. female epigynum, ventral view; F, Female internal genitalia, dorsal view. The arrow points to the retrolateral projection of the VTA. The embolus can be seen arising close to the conductor and through the transparent DTP. Scale bars: A–B, 0.5 mm; C–D, 0.2 mm; E–F = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097229" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097229/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">18C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[151,202,1146,1172]" captionStart="FIGURES 19" captionStartId="35.[151,269,1530,1554]" captionTargetBox="[304,1286,196,1486]" captionTargetId="figure-202@35.[252,1335,124,1506]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURES 19A–E. Architis capricorna Carico. A, male pedipalpus, ventral view; B, male pedipalpus, lateral view; C, female tarsus IV, apex, prolatero-ventral view; D, female epigynum, ventral view; E, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. The arrow points to the retrolateral projection of the VTA. The embolus can be seen arising close to conductor and through the transparent DTP. Scale bars: A–B, 0.2 mm; C–E, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097233" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097233/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">19A</figureCitation>
) and the CD of the female epigynum which is coiled medially of the spermatheca (
<figureCitation box="[1187,1300,1146,1172]" captionStart="FIGURES 16" captionStartId="30.[151,269,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[239,1362,626,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-209@30.[217,1370,606,1871]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURES 16A–D. Architis robusta Carico. A, male pedipalpus, ventral view; B, male pedipalpus, lateral view; C, female epigynum, ventral view; D, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. The arrow points to the retrolateral projection of the VTA. The embolus can be seen arising close to conductor and through the transparent DTP. Scale bars: A–B, 0.2 mm; C–D, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097223/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Figs 16D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1313,1359,1146,1172]" captionStart="FIGURES 18" captionStartId="33.[151,269,1852,1876]" captionTargetBox="[151,1420,193,1790]" captionTargetId="figure-92@33.[140,1447,152,1828]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURES 18A–F. Architis brasiliensis (Mello-Leitão). A, female habitus, dorsal view; B, female prosoma, frontal view; C, male pedipalpus, ventral view, D, male pedipalpus, lateral view, E. female epigynum, ventral view; F, Female internal genitalia, dorsal view. The arrow points to the retrolateral projection of the VTA. The embolus can be seen arising close to the conductor and through the transparent DTP. Scale bars: A–B, 0.5 mm; C–D, 0.2 mm; E–F = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097229" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097229/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">18F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1372,1423,1146,1172]" captionStart="FIGURES 19" captionStartId="35.[151,269,1530,1554]" captionTargetBox="[304,1286,196,1486]" captionTargetId="figure-202@35.[252,1335,124,1506]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURES 19A–E. Architis capricorna Carico. A, male pedipalpus, ventral view; B, male pedipalpus, lateral view; C, female tarsus IV, apex, prolatero-ventral view; D, female epigynum, ventral view; E, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. The arrow points to the retrolateral projection of the VTA. The embolus can be seen arising close to conductor and through the transparent DTP. Scale bars: A–B, 0.2 mm; C–E, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097233" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097233/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">19E</figureCitation>
). These species can be distinguished by the longer vRTA and the smaller and un-notched VTA in the male pedipalpus (
<figureCitation box="[246,397,1226,1252]" captionStart="FIGURES 16" captionStartId="30.[151,269,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[239,1362,626,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-209@30.[217,1370,606,1871]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURES 16A–D. Architis robusta Carico. A, male pedipalpus, ventral view; B, male pedipalpus, lateral view; C, female epigynum, ventral view; D, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. The arrow points to the retrolateral projection of the VTA. The embolus can be seen arising close to conductor and through the transparent DTP. Scale bars: A–B, 0.2 mm; C–D, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097223/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Figs 16A, B</figureCitation>
) of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Carico. A" authorityYear="1981" box="[452,576,1226,1251]" class="Arachnida" family="Pisauridae" genus="Architis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robusta">
<emphasis box="[452,576,1226,1251]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">A. robusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Females present loosely coiled CD and large oval spermathecae (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 16" captionStartId="30.[151,269,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[239,1362,626,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-209@30.[217,1370,606,1871]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURES 16A–D. Architis robusta Carico. A, male pedipalpus, ventral view; B, male pedipalpus, lateral view; C, female epigynum, ventral view; D, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. The arrow points to the retrolateral projection of the VTA. The embolus can be seen arising close to conductor and through the transparent DTP. Scale bars: A–B, 0.2 mm; C–D, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097223/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Fig. 16D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1436,1066,2012]" box="[199,344,1306,1332]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,344,1306,1332]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1436,1066,2012]" box="[199,839,1346,1372]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,262,1346,1372]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Male</emphasis>
(based on IBSP 15158 from Porto Velho, 
<collectingCountry box="[757,830,1346,1372]" name="Brazil" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Brazil</collectingCountry>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1436,1066,2012]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Carapace orange with a pair of lateral longitudinal bands of white scales. Anterior eye row procurved, eyes of similar size. Posterior eyes of similar size, slightly larger than anterior eyes (
<bibRefCitation author="Carico, J. E." box="[1157,1308,1426,1452]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="140 - 153" refId="ref25013" refString="Carico, J. E. (1981) The Neotropical spider genera Architis and Staberius (Pisauridae). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 170, 140 - 153." type="journal article" year="1981">Carico 1981</bibRefCitation>
: figs 5, 8). Sides and posterior margin of carapace covered with dark setae. Chelicerae, labium, and endites orange, sternum pale orange. Pedipalpi cream-coloured, legs pale orange, with darker tibia, metatarsus and tarsus. Opisthosoma dorsally yellow, covered with dark setae and with a median dark gray band and four posterior dark chevrons; laterally dark gray, venter gray with a pair of large yellow spots. Spinnerets orange. Total length 4.5; carapace 2.1 long, 1.9 wide. Tibia I length 2.8, II 2.7, III 1.8, IV 1.9. Opisthosoma 2.4 long, 1.5 wide. dRTA large, conductor robust, gently curved prolaterally (
<figureCitation box="[902,1048,1666,1692]" captionStart="FIGURES 16" captionStartId="30.[151,269,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[239,1362,626,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-209@30.[217,1370,606,1871]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURES 16A–D. Architis robusta Carico. A, male pedipalpus, ventral view; B, male pedipalpus, lateral view; C, female epigynum, ventral view; D, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. The arrow points to the retrolateral projection of the VTA. The embolus can be seen arising close to conductor and through the transparent DTP. Scale bars: A–B, 0.2 mm; C–D, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097223/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Figs 16A, B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1436,1066,2012]" box="[199,1036,1706,1732]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,290,1706,1732]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Female</emphasis>
(based on IBSP 45230 from Reserva Biológica do Una, 
<collectingCountry box="[955,1028,1706,1732]" name="Brazil" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Brazil</collectingCountry>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1436,1066,2012]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Colouration and eye configuration as in male. Total length 5.4; carapace 2.4 long, 2.0 wide. Tibia I length 2.9, II 2.8, III 2.0, IV 1.9. Opisthosoma 3.0 long, 1.6 wide. Lateral lobes of epigynum concave, ventrally and posteriorly projected (
<figureCitation box="[410,518,1826,1852]" captionStart="FIGURES 16" captionStartId="30.[151,269,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[239,1362,626,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-209@30.[217,1370,606,1871]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURES 16A–D. Architis robusta Carico. A, male pedipalpus, ventral view; B, male pedipalpus, lateral view; C, female epigynum, ventral view; D, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. The arrow points to the retrolateral projection of the VTA. The embolus can be seen arising close to conductor and through the transparent DTP. Scale bars: A–B, 0.2 mm; C–D, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097223/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Fig. 16C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1436,1066,2012]" box="[199,939,1866,1892]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,324,1866,1892]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Variation.</emphasis>
Males, total length 4.5–5.3, carapace width 1.9–2.1.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1436,1066,2012]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,398,1906,1932]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Natural history.</emphasis>
Specimens from Una (IBSP 45230, 45231, 45529) were collected by beating understorey vegetation during the day.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
